modules.description: Installs a custom printer for a specific path and type expression, allowing formatted output of values. Removes previously installed printers using a path. Converts untyped exceptions and values into an output format suitable for interactive environments.

Prints any OCaml value with a customizable format, supporting nested structures and type-specific rendering. Operates on arbitrary OCaml values, including tuples, lists, and records, via a PPX syntax extension. Enables debugging by outputting structured data directly from within function bodies or complex expressions.

Provides functions to manipulate file paths, manage environment variables, and process OCaml syntax trees. Works with strings, references, location data, and ppxlib structures. Used to generate print statements, expand or remove printers, and handle file loading paths during code transformation.

Injects custom formatting logic into specific type paths, enabling controlled output of values and exceptions. Supports installation, removal, and conversion of untyped data into readable forms. Key operations include `install_printer`, `remove_printer`, and `output_value`. Users can format complex data structures or debug values in real-time environments.
